# EnsembleWorks runtime requirements — the deploy preflight's source of truth.
# Columns: name  constraint(exact|min|present)  version(- if present)  probe...
# The probe is run on the target; the first MAJOR.MINOR[.PATCH] of its output is
# compared per constraint. Bumping an `exact` pin is a deliberate two-repo change
# (here + laingville servers/<host>/bootstrap.sh) — the preflight enforces it.
# Floors below reflect Debian 13 (trixie) shipping versions + our pinned installs.
# bun is NOT required here: deploy.sh only fetches CI-precompiled `bun build
# --compile` binaries (self-contained executables), it never runs bun on the box.
# gh is NOT required either: ew_fetch_release uses plain `curl` against the
# repo's public release-asset URLs (same shape deploy/install.sh uses) — the
# assets are public, so no `gh auth login` bootstrapping is needed on the box.
livekit-server  exact    1.13.1     livekit-server --version
caddy           min      2.7.0      caddy version
cloudflared     min      2024.1.0   cloudflared --version
git             min      2.39.0     git --version
tmux            min      3.3        tmux -V
python3         min      3.11       python3 --version
cc              present  -          cc --version
pkg-config      present  -          pkg-config --version
